  "content": "e::tests --nocapture`\nExpected: all 4 tests PASS\n\n**Step 6: Commit**\n\n```bash\ngit add crates/corvia-kernel/src/rag_pipeline.rs crates/corvia-kernel/src/lib.rs\ngit commit -m \"feat(m3.2): RagPipeline — orchestrator with context() and ask() modes\"\n```\n\n---\n\n## Task 8: Factory Function + create_rag_pipeline\n\nAdd the factory function that auto-selects the right retriever based on available capabilities.\n\n**Files:**\n- Modify: `crates/corvia-kernel/src/lib.rs`\n\n**Step 1: Write the failing test**\n\nAdd to the `#[cfg(test)]` module in `crates/corvia-kernel/src/lib.rs`:\n\n```rust\n    #[tokio::test]\n    async fn test_create_rag_pipeline_without_graph() {\n        let dir = tempfile::tempdir().unwrap();\n        let mut config = CorviaConfig::default();\n        config.storage.data_dir = dir.path().to_string_lossy().to_string();\n\n        let store = create_store(&config).await.unwrap();\n        let store: Arc<dyn traits::QueryableStore> = store.into();\n        store.init_schema().await.unwrap();\n        let engine: Arc<dyn traits::InferenceEngine> = Arc::new(\n            ollama_engine::OllamaEngine::new(\n                &config.embedding.url,\n                &config.embedding.model,\n                config.embedding.dimensions,\n            )\n        );\n\n        let pipeline = create_rag_pipeline(store, engine, None, None, &config);\n        // Should use VectorRetriever when no graph is available\n        assert!(pipeline.retriever_name() == \"vector\");\n    }\n```\n\n**Step 2: Run test to verify it fails**\n\nRun: `cargo test -p corvia-kernel -- tests::test_create_rag_pipeline --nocapture`\nExpected: FAIL — `create_rag_pipeline` not found\n\n**Step 3: Add factory function and retriever_name accessor**\n\nIn `crates/corvia-kernel/src/lib.rs`, add the factory function after the existing `create_store` function:\n\n```rust\n/// Create a RAG pipeline with auto-selected retriever.\n/// Uses GraphExpandRetriever when a GraphStore is available, VectorRetriever otherwise.\npub fn create_rag_pipeline(",
